 Magill]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1994|11|01}}|caps=49|goals=10|club=[[Everton L.F.C.|Everton]]|clubnat=ENG}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=11|pos=FW|name=[[Lauren Wade]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|11|22}}|caps=19|goals=1|club=[[Glasgow City]]|clubnat=SCO}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=17|pos=FW|name=[[Casey Howe]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|2002|9|2}}|caps=2|goals=0|club=[[Linfield Ladies F.C.|Linfield]]|clubnat=NIR}}\n{{nat fs g player|no=19|pos=FW|name=[[Caitlin McGuinness]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|2002|8|30}}|caps=5|goals=0|club=[[Linfield Ladies F.C.|Linfield]]|clubnat=NIR}}\n{{nat fs end}}\n\n===Recent call-ups===\nThe following players have been named to a squad in the past 12 months.\n\n''This list may be incomplete.''\n\n{{nat fs r start}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=GK|name=[[Lauren Perry]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|2001|4|5}}|caps=6|goals=0|club=[[Blackburn Rovers L.F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]]|clubnat=ENG|latest=v. {{fbw|WAL}}, 12 November 2019}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=GK|name=[[Becky Flaherty|Rebecca Flaherty]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1998|3|6}}|caps=1|goals=0|club=[[Sheffield United W.F.C.|Sheffield United]]|clubnat=ENG|latest=v. {{fbw|WAL}}, 12 November 2019}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=GK|name=[[Emma Higgins]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1986|5|15}}|caps=87|goals=1|club=[[Glentoran W.F.C.|Glentoran]]|clubnat=NIR|latest=v. {{fbw|WAL}}, 3 September 2019}}\n{{nat fs break}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=DF|name=[[Freya Holdaway]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1989|04|12}}|caps=6|goals=0|club=[[Crystal Palace F.C. (Women)|Crystal Palace]]|clubnat=ENG|latest=v. {{fbw|WAL}}, 3 September 2019}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=DF|name=[[Claragh Connor]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1995|5|16}}|caps=0|goals=0|club=[[Sion Swifts Ladies]]|clubnat=NIR|latest=v. {{fbw|WAL}}, 3 September 2019}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=DF|name=[[Natalie Johnson]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|11|12}}|caps=0|goals=0|club=[[Leicester City W.F.C.|Leicester City]]|clubnat=ENG|latest=v. {{fbw|WAL}}, 3 September 2019}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=DF|name=[[Yasmin White]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|2000|07|07}}|caps=0|goals=0|club=[[Glentoran Belfast United L.F.C.|Glentoran Belfast United]]|clubnat=NIR|latest=v. {{fbw|WAL}}, 3 September 2019}}\n{{nat fs break}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=MF|name=[[Kerry Montgomery]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1988|03|25}}|caps=8|goals=0|club=[[Motherwell L.F.C.|Motherwell]]|clubnat=SCO|latest=v. {{fbw|WAL}}, 3 September 2019}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=MF|name=[[Rebecca Holloway]]|age={{birth date and age|df=yes|1995|08|25}}|caps=0|goals=0|club=[[Birmingham City W.F.C.|Birmingham City]]|clubnat=ENG|latest=v. {{fbw|WAL}}, 3 September 2019}}\n{{nat fs end}}\n\n==Player records==\nNorthern Ireland's [[Simone Magill]] holds the world record for the [[Fastest goals in association football|fastest international goal]] in women's football. Previously, US forward [[Alex Morgan]] had held the record at twelve seconds. Magill achieved an eleven-second goal against [[Georgia women's national football team|Georgia]] at the start of a European Qualifying match on 3 June 2016, after chasing down the ball and then receiving a cross from a teammate. The [[Irish Football Association]] awarded her with a special trophy. The goal also marks the fastest ever international goal by any national Northern Irish team \u2013 male or female.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.belfastlive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/now-thats-quick-northern-ireland-13730868|title=Northern Ireland striker recognised for scoring fastest goal ever!|last=Fullerton|first=Gareth|date=7 October 2017|website=belfastlive|access-date=25 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Recent results and schedules==\n{{Main|Northern Ireland women's national football team results}}\n\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Lose|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\nThe following is a list of matches in the last 12 months, as well as any future matches that have been scheduled.\n\n===2020===\n{{Footballbox collapsible\n| format       = 1\n| round        = [[2020_Pinatar_Cup#Standings|2020 Pinatar Cup]]\n| date         = 4 March 2020\n| time         = 14:00\n| referee      = Zuzana Valentov\u00e1 ([[Slovak Football Association|Slovakia]])\n| team1        = {{fbw-rt|NIR}}\n| goals1       = \n| score        = 0\u20131\n| result       = L\n| report       = https://www.irishfa.com/news/2020/march/pinatar-cup-northern-ireland-senior-women-edged-out-by-iceland\n| team2        = {{fbw|ISL}}\n| goals2       = [[Dagn\u00fd Brynjarsd\u00f3ttir|Brynjarsd\u00f3ttir]] {{goal|23}}\n| location     = [[San Pedro del Pinatar]], [[Spain]]\n| stadium      = [[Pinatar Arenal]]\n| attendance   = \n}}\n\n==Competitive record==\n===World Cup===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; width:50%;\"   \n|-\n!colspan=10|World Cup Finals\n|-\n!Year\n!Result\n!GP\n!W\n!D*\n!L\n!GF\n!GA\n!GD\n|-   \n||{{flagicon|China|}} [[1991 FIFA Women's World Cup|1991]]||''Did Not Qualify''||-||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-     \n||{{flagicon|Sweden}} [[1995 FIFA Women's World Cup|1995]]||''Did Not Enter''||-||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-   \n||{{flagicon|USA}} [[1999 FIFA Women's World Cup|1999]]||''Did Not Enter''||-||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n||{{flagicon|USA}} [[2003 FIFA Women's World Cup|2003]]||''Did Not Enter''||-||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n||{{flagicon|China}} [[2007 FIFA Women's World Cup|2007]]||''Did Not Qualify''||-||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n||{{flagicon|Germany}} [[2011 FIFA Women's World Cup|2011]]||''Did Not Qualify''||-||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n||{{flagicon|Canada}} [[2015 FIFA Women's World Cup|2015]]||''Did Not Qualify''||-||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n||{{flagicon|France}} [[2019 FIFA Women's World Cup|2019]]||''Did Not Qualify''||-||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|-\n|'''Total'''||0/8||-||-||-||-||-||-||-\n|}\n:''*Draws include knockout matches decided on [[penalty shootout (football)|penalty kicks