to co-produce content for Noggin.<ref>{{cite news |title=Nickelodeon Buys Out Noggin; Enters Into Production Deal With Sesame Workshop |url=http://www.awn.com/news/nickelodeon-buys-out-noggin-enters-production-deal-sesame-workshop |last=Godfrey |first=Leigh |date=August 9, 2002 |work=[[Animation World Network]]}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:75%;text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:25%;\" | Title !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10%;\" | First air date !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10%;\" | Last air date\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[A Walk In Your Shoes]]'' || {{dts|May 1, 2000}} || {{dts|March 31, 2002}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Jack's Big Music Show]]'' || {{dts|September 12, 2005}}<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20050823000214/http://www.noggin.com:80/shows/jacks.php</ref> || {{dts|October 13, 2007}} (first-run)<br/>{{dts|September 27, 2009}}<ref name=\"aug2009\"/>{{refn|group=note|name=Nick Jr. channel|This show continued to air on the same channel when Noggin was re-branded as [[Nick Jr.]] from September 28, 2009 onward.}} (reruns)\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''On the Team'' || {{dts|January 30, 2001}} || {{dts|March 31, 2002}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Oobi (TV series)|Oobi]]'' || {{dts|2000}} || {{dts|February 11, 2005}}<ref name=\"oobi-ending\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/oobi/episode-4488081/203580/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160627011809/http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/oobi/episode-4488081/203580/|archivedate=June 27, 2016|title=''Oobi'' \u2013 Chez Oobi!; Valentine!|date=February 11, 2005|work=[[TV Guide]]|publisher=[[CBS Corporation]]|accessdate=June 27, 2016}}</ref> (first-run)<br/>{{dts|September 27, 2009}}<ref name=\"aug2009\"/>{{refn|group=note|name=Nick Jr. channel}} (reruns)\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Phred on Your Head Show]]'' || {{dts|July 26, 1999}} || {{dts|March 31, 2002}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Play with Me Sesame]]''{{refn|group=note|name=pwms|Co-produced by Sesame Workshop and Nick Digital for Noggin Originals.}} || {{dts|April 1, 2002}} || {{dts|September 10, 2007}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Sponk!]]'' || {{dts|September 10, 2001}} || {{dts|March 31, 2002}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[The Upside Down Show]]''{{refn|group=note|name=upside|Co-produced by Noggin LLC and Sesame Workshop for Nickelodeon Preschool, despite the show being Australian; both companies co-own the copyright.}} || {{dts|October 16, 2006}}<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20060830221434/http://www.noggin.com/shows/upsidedown.php</ref> || {{dts|September 27, 2009}}<ref name=\"aug2009\"/>{{refn|group=note|name=Nick Jr. channel}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[The URL with Phred Show]]'' || {{dts|September 10, 2001}} || {{dts|March 31, 2002}}\n|}\n\n===Sesame Workshop library===\nReruns of series from Sesame Workshop's content library were shown as a staple of Noggin from 1999 to 2005.<ref name=\"Gerbarg1999\">{{cite book|author=Darcy Gerbarg|title=The Economics, Technology and Content of Digital TV|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jqQuDKkdhgwC&pg=PA246|date=31 January 1999|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|isbn=978-0-7923-8325-3|pages=246\u2013}}</ref> Two syndication packages of ''Sesame Street'' episodes, titled ''Sesame Street Unpaved'' and ''123 Sesame Street'', were created specifically by and for Noggin LLC.<ref>{{cite web|title=Noggin Celebrates Mom Sunday, May 11 with Themed Episodes of Preschool Favorites|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/noggin-celebrates-mom-sunday-may-11-with-themed-episodes-of-preschool-favorites-55492867.html|work=[[PR Newswire]]|publisher=[[Cision Inc.]]|date=May 2, 2003}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:75%;text-align:ce